{"key":"processedPost-10057521","value":{"id":10057521,"first":10056857,"last":10099242,"when":1238217829,"utime":"03/28/09 08:23 AM","content":"I use a flowhood, so I simply lift the lid off and pour the water right in from jar to jar, and jar to flask.&nbsp; By the time you guys get into bulk growing where you want that much LC, you really need to pony up the dough for a flowhood.<br />Mostly, I just use that tek to make syringes for demonstrating the brf tek at schools and such.&nbsp; For my own growing, I do grain inoculations in quart jars from agar wedges, and when those are grown out and tested, I do grain to grain transfers into filter patch bags of rye that hold 6 to 7 quarts.&nbsp; Each of those rye bags will inoculate 20 more, so I can expand mycelium WAY faster that way than by using LC.&nbsp; Syringes are for kids.<br />RR","title":"Re: Kick-Ass Sounding LC Method I Gotta Try"}}